# ============================================================
# park.dlg  —  Comprehensive example scene
# One file = one scene/view (the park).
# Each [interaction] is a separate dialogue graph.
# ============================================================

# Scene-wide background defaults.
# Any character listed here gets this bg unless overridden locally.
@bg Akihiko   bgAkihiko
@bg Yuki      bgYuki
@bg Guard     bgGuard

== Scene: Riverside Park ==

# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 4 — Three-way conversation, multiple characters
# The player stumbles into an argument between Yuki and the Guard.
# ============================================================

[interaction: yuki_guard_argument | Yuki arguing with a guard at the gate]

Guard: Ma'am, the east path is closed after sundown. I've said it twice.
Yuki: And I've told you — I left my bag on the bench. It will take thirty seconds.
Guard: Rules are rules. Come back tomorrow.

# Player arrives
Akihiko: Hey, what's going on?
Yuki: This guard won't let me through to get my bag.
Guard: Sir, please stay back. This doesn't concern you.

Akihiko: Can we work something out here?

[choice]
    > Vouch for Yuki     -> @vouch
    > Side with the guard -> @side_guard
    > Stay out of it      -> @stay_out

@vouch
Akihiko: I know her. She's not going to cause any trouble.
Guard: ...
Guard: Fine. Two minutes. And you're coming with her.
Yuki: Thank you.
Yuki(bgYukiClose): ...Both of you.
[end]

@side_guard
Akihiko: He's got a point, Yuki. Come back in the morning.
Yuki: Are you serious right now?
Yuki(bgYukiClose): Fine. Don't talk to me tonight.
[end]

@stay_out
Akihiko: Actually — yeah, none of my business. Carry on.
Guard: Smart man.
Yuki: Unbelievable.
[end]
